# Cloudflare Pages custom headers.
#
# Anti-discovery firewall (see mind-map project_blog_launch): the blog is
# intentionally hostile to crawlers, indexers, and training-set aggregators.
# Distribution is word of mouth only. The portfolio (/) stays permissive and
# acts as the sole discoverable on-ramp; /blog/* and the FortyAU-internal
# kimmy deck (/my-work/kimmy/*) are firewalled.
#
# This is the edge-enforced layer on the portfolio origin. It complements —
# and does not replace — the robots.txt disallow. A header is honored even
# when a crawler ignores robots.txt.
#
# The blog content itself is served by the Bludit CMS at blog.thetyster.dev
# (the landing-page list links out to it); crawler defense for the posts
# themselves is enforced on that origin. These /blog* rules keep any residual
# /blog path on the portfolio origin (e.g. a redirect stub) out of indexes.
#
# @cloudflare/next-on-pages appends its own autogenerated immutable-asset
# block below this file's contents at build; both are served.

/blog
  X-Robots-Tag: noindex, nofollow

/blog/*
  X-Robots-Tag: noindex, nofollow

# kimmy is FortyAU-internal work: reachable via the portfolio, but kept out of
# indexes and training sets like the blog.
/my-work/kimmy/*
  X-Robots-Tag: noindex, nofollow

# The orbital-shifting deck carries the philosophy content the firewall exists
# to protect from training-set absorption and flattening. Reachable via the
# portfolio hero tile, but kept out of indexes and training sets.
/my-work/orbital-shifting/*
  X-Robots-Tag: noindex, nofollow
